OL,6,FRAC road safety spokesman Rod Dennis
OL,7,Fsaid: "It's chilling to see a
OL,8,Fproportion of the driving public
OL,9,Fremain intent on taking charge of a
OL,10,Fcar while intoxicated, even after
OL,11,Fthey've already been caught by the
OL,12,Fpolice on at least one occasion.
OL,14,F"The rate of fatalities caused by
OL,15,Fpeople drinking and driving is now at
OL,16,Fa similar level to where it was in the
OL,17,Flate 1980s, so it's clear something
OL,18,Fneeds to change.
