OL,4,Cdriving four times or more
OL,6,F"Drivers need to be prevented from
OL,7,Fdrinking and driving in the first
OL,8,Fplace, so there's a good argument for
OL,9,Fmandating alcolocks be fitted to
OL,10,Fvehicles driven by anyone previously
OL,11,Fconvicted."
OL,13,FWilliam Porter, policy and
OL,14,Fcommunications manager at road safety
OL,15,Fcharity IAM RoadSmart, said: "The
OL,16,Fsheer scale of reoffending is deeply
OL,17,Ftroubling and demonstrates the need to
OL,18,Fre-evaluate our approach to reducing
OL,19,Fdrink-driving.
