OL,4,Cdriving four times or more
OL,6,F"Measures should include an expansion
OL,7,Fof drink-drive rehabilitation courses
OL,8,Fwhich lower the rate of reoffending
OL,9,Famong those who take them against
OL,10,Fthose who do not.
OL,12,F"Additionally, serious consideration
OL,13,Fshould be given to require repeat
OL,14,Foffenders to have alcolocks fitted to
OL,15,Ftheir vehicle."
OL,17,FMr Porter added: "Increasing the
OL,18,Fnumber of roadside breathalyser tests
OL,19,Fcarried out by police would also
OL,20,Fprovide a visual deterrent for those
OL,21,Fthinking about risking it."
